5|$|Besides {{her success}} in the United Kingdom, Heyer's novels were very popular in the United States and Germany and {{achieved}} respectable sales in Czechoslovakia. A first printing {{of one of her}} novels in the Commonwealth often consisted of 65,000–75,000 copies, and her novels collectively sold over 100,000copies in <b>hardback</b> each year. Her paperbacks usually sold over 500,000copies each. At the time of her death 48 of her books were still in print, including her first novel, The Black Moth.|$|E
